# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-upgrade

Model/effort: Sonnet / high.

The down-sync. Pulls approved framework improvements from the hub into this brain without
disturbing project-owned work. Follows the propagation contract; lands via PR.

## Steps
1. OPEN-lite: read the operating contract §7 and the propagation contract; state the upgrade
   objective.
2. Resolve the gap: compare the hub registry `brain-factory/registry/framework-version.json`
   against the brain manifest `framework_version`. If equal, report "up to date" and stop.
3. Collect deltas: read each intervening release note from current (exclusive) to latest
   (inclusive); note each changed core module and its change kind.
4. Build the upgrade plan: skip disabled core modules; surface `adopted: false` artifacts as
   manual-review; stage the rest from the hub brain template.
5. Apply core-layer deltas. PRESERVE all extensions — never touch `extensions` paths; surface
   any collision for operator review. Bump `synced_from` and set manifest
   `framework_version = latest`.
6. CLOSE ritual: append a continuity entry describing the upgrade; regenerate the capabilities
   map; run the test suite the way the project runs it; open the change as a PR and push.

## Done when
The manifest is at the latest framework version, core deltas are applied with extensions
intact, and the upgrade is in a PR with validation evidence.
